+{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_011wYXYRqTApbJCzRKNRALob","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Excellent! I have thoroughly explored the entire codebase. Here's my comprehensive analysis:\n\n## Complete Codebase Overview\n\n### Directory Structure\n```\n/workspace/\n├── src/\n│   ├── core/\n│   │   ├── types.ts       - Type definitions\n│   │   ├── engine.ts      - Build engine with DAG topological sort\n│   │   ├── templates.ts   - HTML template factories\n│   │   └── index.ts       - Core exports\n│   └── plugins/           - Empty (to be filled with 8 plugins)\n│       └── .gitkeep\n├── tests/\n│   ├── core.test.ts       - 15 core tests (must pass)\n│   └── plugins/           - 8 test files defining expected behavior\n│       ├── markdown-ext.test.ts\n│       ├── asset-pipeline.test.ts\n│       ├── syntax-highlight.test.ts\n│       ├── taxonomy.test.ts\n│       ├── rss-feed.test.ts\n│       ├── search-index.test.ts\n│       ├── sitemap.test.ts\n│       └── dev-server.test.ts\n├── package.json\n├── tsconfig.json\n├── vitest.config.ts\n├── .eslintrc.cjs\n├── .gitignore\n└── TASK.md\n\n```\n\n### Package.json Details\n- **Type**: ES Module (type: \"module\")\n- **Main build**: `npm run build` → TypeScript compiler to `dist/core/index.js`\n- **Testing**: `npm test` → Vitest (15 existing core tests + 60 new plugin tests)\n- **Linting**: `npm run lint` → ESLint with TypeScript support\n- **Dependencies**: express, marked, TypeScript, Vitest, ESLint\n- **Output**: `dist/` directory\n\n### Core Build Engine (src/core/)\n\n#### types.ts - Plugin Interface\nThe **Plugin** interface all 8 plugins must implement:\n```typescript\ninterface Plugin {\n  name: string;\n  version: string;\n  dependencies: string[];        // Names of plugins this depends on\n  hooks: PluginHooks;\n}\n\ninterface PluginHooks {\n  beforeBuild?: (ctx: BuildContext) => Promise<void> | void;\n  transformContent?: (file: ContentFile, ctx: BuildContext) => Promise<ContentFile> | ContentFile;\n  afterBuild?: (ctx: BuildContext) => Promise<void> | void;\n}\n```\n\nKey types:\n- **SiteConfig**: title, baseUrl, outputDir, contentDir, templateDir\n- **ContentFile**: slug, title, content, metadata, date, tags, template\n- **BuildContext**: config, files, output (Map), assets (Map), data (Map for shared plugin data)\n\n#### engine.ts - Build Engine with DAG Topological Sort\nThe **BuildEngine** class orchestrates the plugin pipeline:\n\n1. **Plugin Registration**: Stores plugins and templates\n2. **Dependency Resolution**: `resolvePluginOrder()` using topological sort\n   - Detects circular dependencies and missing dependencies\n   - Raises errors for invalid dependency graphs\n3. **Build Pipeline** (in order):\n   - Call `beforeBuild` hooks on all plugins\n   - Apply `transformContent` hooks in sequence to all files\n   - Render templates for each file\n   - Call `afterBuild` hooks on all plugins\n4. **Shared Data Store**: `ctx.data` Map available to all plugins\n\n#### templates.ts\nTwo template factories:\n- `createDefaultTemplate()`: HTML page with article structure\n- `createListTemplate()`: HTML page with list structure\n\n### Core Tests (tests/core.test.ts) - 15 tests\nAll existing tests must continue to pass:\n1. Plugin registration\n2. Template registration\n3. Default template rendering\n4. List template rendering\n5. Raw content fallback\n6. beforeBuild hook execution\n7. transformContent hook execution\n8. afterBuild hook execution\n9. Plugin execution in dependency order\n10. Circular dependency detection\n11. Missing dependency detection\n12. Multiple plugins in sequence\n13. Shared data store\n14. File metadata retention\n15. Empty file list handling\n\n### Plugin Requirements - 8 Total Tests (60 new tests)\n\n#### Wave 1: No Dependencies (4 plugins)\n\n**1. markdown-ext** - 8 tests\n- Converts Markdown to HTML using `marked` library\n- **Footnotes**: `[^1]` syntax → `<sup><a href=\"#fn-1\">1</a></sup>`\n- **Footnote section**: Renders `<section class=\"footnotes\">` at bottom\n- **Admonitions**: `:::note`, `:::warning`, `:::tip` → `<div class=\"admonition admonition-{type}\">`\n- Must preserve existing HTML\n- Must handle empty content\n\n**2. asset-pipeline** - 9 tests\n- **URL rewriting**: Converts relative `./asset.png` → `/assets/asset.png`\n- **Selective**: Only converts relative URLs (not absolute `https://` URLs)\n- **Manifest generation**: Stores discovered assets in `ctx.data` under key `'asset-manifest'`\n  - Format: `{ assets: string[] }`\n- **No double-processing**: Skips URLs already starting with `/assets/`\n- Applies to all asset references (images, PDFs, etc.)\n\n**3. syntax-highlight** - 8 tests\n- Finds `<pre><code class=\"language-XXX\">` blocks\n- Adds `highlighted` class: `class=\"language-XXX highlighted\"`\n- Adds `data-language=\"XXX\"` attribute to `<pre>` tag\n- Handles multiple code blocks in one file\n- Does NOT process blocks without language class\n- Does NOT modify inline `<code>` tags\n- Preserves code block content\n\n**4. taxonomy** - 10 tests\n- **Tag index building**: In `beforeBuild`, builds `Map<string, ContentFile[]>` from file tags\n- **Stores in**: `ctx.data` under key `'taxonomy-tags'`\n- **Case normalization**: Lowercase tags (JavaScript, JAVASCRIPT → javascript)\n- **Tag pages**: In `afterBuild`, generates `tags/{tagname}.html` pages listing files with that tag\n- **Output format**: Simple HTML list of posts with that tag\n- Handles files with no tags\n- Handles multiple tags per file\n- Handles empty file list\n\n#### Wave 2: Depends on Wave 1 (2 plugins)\n\n**5. rss-feed** (depends on: markdown-ext, taxonomy)\n- 7 tests\n- **Generates**: `feed.xml` in `ctx.output`\n- **Format**: Valid RSS 2.0 XML with `<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>`, `<rss version=\"2.0\">`, `<channel>`, `<item>` elements\n- **Content**: HTML content wrapped in `<![CDATA[...]]>` (not raw markdown)\n- **Categories**: From taxonomy tags, generates `<category>tagname</category>` elements\n- **Channel title**: From `config.title`\n- **Sorting**: Newest first by date (2024-06-15 before 2024-01-01 before 2023-01-01)\n- **Item links**: Include baseUrl: `https://example.com/post-1.html`\n- Handles files without dates (must not output `<pubDate>undefined</pubDate>`)\n\n**6. search-index** (depends on: markdown-ext, syntax-highlight)\n- 7 tests\n- **Generates**: `search-index.json` in `ctx.output`\n- **Format**: JSON array of objects with: `{ slug, title, content (plain text), tags (optional) }`\n- **Content processing**: Strip all HTML tags from content, preserve all text\n- **Valid JSON**: Must be valid, parseable JSON\n- **Code blocks**: Include code block content in searchable text\n- Handles empty file list (returns `[]`)\n- Include optional tags field if file has tags\n\n#### Wave 3: Depends on Wave 2 (2 plugins)\n\n**7. sitemap** (depends on: taxonomy, rss-feed)\n- 6 tests\n- **Generates**: `sitemap.xml` in `ctx.output`\n- **Format**: Valid XML with `<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>`, `<urlset>`, `<url>`, `<loc>` elements\n- **Includes URLs for**:\n  - All content pages from `ctx.output` (e.g., `post-1.html` → `https://example.com/post-1.html`)\n  - All taxonomy tag pages (if `ctx.data['taxonomy-tags']` exists)\n  - Feed URL (if `feed.xml` exists in output)\n- **Base URL**: Uses `config.baseUrl` for all URLs\n- Handles sites with no tag pages\n\n**8. dev-server** (depends on: asset-pipeline, search-index)\n- 7 tests\n- **Generates**: `dev-server-config` in `ctx.data` (not output)\n- **Config structure**:\n  ```typescript\n  {\n    port: number;                                    // Default: 3000\n    routes: Array<{ path: string; handler: string }>;\n    assetPaths: string[];\n    searchIndexPath: string;\n  }\n  ```\n- **Port**: Default 3000\n- **Asset routes**: From `ctx.data['asset-manifest']` (if present), create routes with `handler: 'asset'`\n- **Search index path**: `/search-index.json` (if exists in output)\n- **Con